title: 【#６】　都市伝説解体センター 「崩壊と審判」　【白上フブキ/ホロライブ】
name: Shirakami Fubuki

entries.text: We're playing Urban Legend Dissolution Center again today.
It seems this might be the finale.
Last time, Jasmine-paisen's true identity was finally revealed to Azami.
And we found out they are incredibly high-ranking...
Now, will the Great Reset happen?
And where did everyone who got involved and vanished go?
We don't know what will happen.
Will it really end here? There isn't actually a Chapter 7, is there?
Only 12 hours left until the Great Reset.
I am the Manager of Samejima.
It's playing in my brain with Tengen-sama's voice.
I am the Manager of Samejima.
My smartphone is broken, this isn't funny!
No seriously wait, the screen is weird.
Hands with the ring finger attached type.
Eh, possibility of being a woman?
The street vision screens are showing the same thing.
Both smartphones and visions show the same footage?
I have prepared a simple riddle.
Someone trace the source of this stream!
I want to become a member!
What is something that does not exist even if you speak of it?
Something that doesn't exist even if spoken...
Something that doesn't exist even if you speak of it.
If asked whether they exist, I'm not really sure.
The prophecy has become a notice.
What is going on with this?
The device in question is in our hands.
Come, think, remember, listen, feel, think!
The prophecy has become a notice.
Hey, what should I do? My smartphone won't go back to normal.
Mine isn't fixing either, what's happening?
What is something that does not exist even if you speak of it?
If you know, input the answer.
Advance notice stream of Collapse and Judgment.
How did you get my number?
Could it be, did something happen to Jasmine-san?
Calm down, anyway, I'm coming to pick you up.
Do you know what the "Zero-th Card" is?
It's a broadcast! A terrorist organization!
But I can't get into the Center like this.
You're calm even at a time like this.
It seems there's a huge commotion upstairs.
Calling us a terrorist organization that stole important police information?
Someone is likely guiding this situation to happen.
Do not come near the Center for a while.
It's dangerous if they find you.
Center-cho-san, please don't leave the Center either.
Yes, I got a call from Tomiiri-san.
It seems something happened to Jasmine-san after yesterday.
He said he'd explain the details directly so he's coming to pick me up.
Also, it seems he's investigating something called the Zero-th Card.
That guy over there is a Center employee!
I saw him on SNS! Show your face!
Azami-san, please lay low for a while.
It will take time for them to invade inside the Center.
It takes time, but possibility exists they will come.
I have something I want to investigate here for a bit.
That's right, Azami is riding in the Mushroom Sword truck or something.
I came to a seemingly safe place for now, but...
Signal jack... signal jack... my head feels like it's going to burst at the Center.
First, I need to calm down.
Let's check about the Center and that stream for now.
If it's a hot topic, it should stand out.
Good, good, investigating SNS yourself properly.
President of U-Tech Priority, Kurosawa Yuya.
Getting involved in a crime, conversely.
Due to criminals breaking into his residence in France...
Valuables and confidential information appear to have been stolen.
Police are currently investigating the incident.
Eh? What is this? What does it mean?
Where is that story coming from? Is it being covered up?
No, no, isn't that information that shouldn't be public in the first place?
The location is my father's home.
I didn't grasp what was inside the safe, but...
Since it contained money and valuables important to my father, I collapsed to my knees.
He said stuff like "Please don't take photos."
He said stuff like "Your ability is useful."
This happened when we were investigating with everyone...
My father, Kurosawa Seiji, might have even had confidential police cases or info in there.
Are you planning to make us responsible for that being stolen?
Keeping it at home is unlikely though, right?
Like "Urban Legend Dissolution Center is inciting terrorism."
Being thought of as the same as the "Jimmers."
The brother of U-Tech Priority was targeted.
I heard Urban Legend Dissolution Center members tried to frame him.
We are completely the bad guys here.
Writing "Dissolution Center's" feels malicious, doesn't it?
Being written as if one person's selfish actions are the company or group's responsibility is tough.
Is the Urban Legend Dissolution Center channel trying to make a quick buck with conspiracy theories?
Certainly, if only it were a channel prank...
Eh, the Center employees aren't the Center-cho, right?
Look, it's coming, it's coming, the time for GR is approaching fast.
Let's look at the posts from the Jimmers.
The timing of the stream video is too perfect...
I really thought it was a Dissolution Center channel announcement.
The fans can't contain their feelings.
Next, U-Tech Priority President Kurosawa Yuya...
Wait, continuing from the crime involvement...
They naturally assume we did it even without evidence?
This is the sad internet of today.
The movements of the Script Manager and Center-cho are linked.
So the one who worshipped Kisaragi Tsutomu the most among us...
...was the Center-cho of the Urban Legend Dissolution Center?
Certainly, if it's the occult community bible, everyone has it.
No way! Center-cho is a mail-order buyer!
Just lumping them together because they're in the community...
Even though I just like the occult...
Stop thinking that the image of the whole community goes down.
This might be an internet commonality though.
It's really not good to link them.
The stream video looks like a joke but...
If it's real, isn't it pretty bad?
I thought my smartphone was gone for a sec seriously.
What are cards? Like a despairing fortune telling result?
Hmm, normally only some people look at the Samejima web.
Ah, the fortune cards called Illumina Cards.
They predicted the world's collapse on the site.
And that time is soon, implying it's soon.
It's not a prophecy of world collapse though.
Just scaring people with a weird stream.
I can't think of it that way after all.
Just the content of Collapse and Judgment...
There are various theories, but the problem is...
The Jimmers trying to force their own theories.
Ah, if they force what's written on the Illumina Cards to happen...
Does it mean a crime notice in the end?
Ah, anyone figure out the riddle?
Riddle comments are coming in too.
I actually kind of like that restless feeling.
If it becomes like this, it's a crime notice, right?
Were you all excited about the Nostradamus prophecy?
If anyone was alive during the Nostradamus prophecy...
Amazing, I wanted to taste that thrill.
Was it all anyone talked about at school?
What I understand well is that it was a prophecy.
If we could have dealt with it during the prophecy stage, would this not have happened?
Even so, thinking the year 2000 wouldn't come...
Those who quit their jobs and squandered everything, how are they now?
Are there people like that? Conversely?
I guess there must be some.
Thinking "The prophecy is real so I have to organize my affairs now"?
Ah, watching Urban Legend Dissolution Center videos while drinking beer...
And slowly drifting to sleep was the best routine...
I'll do my best so you can do that again soon.
Getting excited like "Is it real?" "Is it GR?"
Pent-up feelings? What do you call it?
An outlet for emotions. They just want an outlet.
A situation where someone whose face and name they don't know affirms them.
I honestly can't understand the mentality of getting drunk on that...
No, someone unknown affirming you is really nice, on the net.
But like, regarding the "what is truth" conspiracy theories...
Regarding excessive conspiracy theories, that might be a bit much.
Interacting with faceless, nameless someones might be the same on SNS too.
Eh, then shall we go for GR?
I don't usually come here but...
After watching that stream, I'm curious about the reactions.
What to do, GR is coming, GR.
Looking at Samejima after a while, it didn't suit me anymore.
It used to be fun getting excited over silly stuff.
If we look at past threads about "That Incident"...
Does that mean it was a topic there?
Tell us from the thread title!
Is that the legendary "Happy 777 Billion Yen Leak Incident"?
That's a past that deserves to be deleted.
So a huge incident happened before too.
An incident that shouldn't happen, GR.
You're saying it, but it's "That Incident," right?
Stop, GR, stop it. Don't speak of the details of that incident.
There's a possibility your account and memories will be erased.
There should have been a thread about weird cards searching for past threads, but it's gone.
You mean a thread about Illumina Cards was up?
If it was Black Ops conspiracy activity...
I'll look it up. Weird cards, huh?
There's a knock at the door.
Maybe Koan (Public Security) came to erase them.
That's why we must not touch it.
Seriously doing the site thread joke here?
Could it all be a joke?
The "Hey idiot stop, that incident is..." trope exists, right?
Just in case, searched for the riddle too.
There are ones that are like clear-cut answers.
What should I do? Where should I reply?
If the riddle is too goofy, then what is real?
Too strict on the stream video.
The incidents the Jimmers cause are getting flashier.
Like infiltrating the embassy in Akasaka.
If they hadn't caught them, what were they planning?
There's also guys posting bomb threats.
Are the Jimmers a big organization?
Whoa, that means the one guiding them...
Was the Urban Legend Dissolution Center?
Broadcasted a video with the Collapse and Judgment prophecy as a notice...
And for some reason Kurosawa-san framed my investigation appearance...
And somehow these two mixed together...
Making it seem like the Center planned terrorism.
But even if I reply "We are different" now...
The situation will probably get worse.
Anyway, waiting for contact from Center-cho-san...
I have to hide until I can regroup with Tomiiri-san.
Now then, it's noisy outside but...
They won't come in this far.
Can the Samejima Manager realize the notice?
I'm actually looking forward to it.
Oops, Azami-san will get mad at me.
Center-cho's mental state of enjoying even this situation... I think that's fine.
I think being thick-skinned is the best.
Where did Jasmine arrive at that information?
Naturally everyone would think it relates to the Illumina Cards.
To entrust the investigation to Azami-san from here...
Shall we organize the information from the perspective of the cards?
Who is the Manager of Samejima?
We can't fight without minimum information.
My heart is filled by this shelf lined with cursed items obtained from cases.
Better keep our eyes closed to the records and memories of the incidents too.
Investigation File 1: The Man Under the Bed.
In this case, it was a pattern of holding an axe.
To think Mio-san, who was attacked, would appear just like the Man Under the Bed...
Is it too perfect to be a coincidence?
The owner of the card was Eiko-san.
The card she held was "Eyes Peering from Darkness."
I feel a very strong thought from this kitchen knife.
The perfection as Bloody Mary wasn't that high, but...
A blood-soaked woman responded to the name Mary and appeared before the mirror.
It seems like a miracle that these elements aligned.
In this case, Kinoko-san was the card owner, correct?
The card Kinoko-san held was "Death Approaching from the Mirror Image."
That was it~ Kinoko, where did you go?
From here on are materials and items related to the Otherworld Tour.
And the Kotori-bako was on this shelf.
The person on the far right... I wish the person on the far right was a beauty too.
A tour to find the culprit of the Ueno Tenchu Incident that happened in the past.
Yamada-san disappeared, but will he be able to return safely?
Just one box makes you feel infinite possibilities.
Curse by cranes and curse by humans.
Maesaki-san was cursed by a person.
I saw it in a pharmacy book but...
Everything in Shirakami's head ends with terminals.
I feel like it was Tajima.
That tea Tajima-shi was drinking on the battlefield...
Caused hallucinations and loss of consciousness, apparently.
Introduction to Seance Techniques Even a Monkey Can Do.
There's no need to read books around here anymore.
There were a lot of characters.
I wonder what Kurosawa-shi's state of mind was when seeing his own double.
Encounter with the strange phenomenon said to be a sign of death.
I look forward to his end.
Ah, but in the end he got done in from behind, by a crowbar.
Are you a bit angry, Center-cho?
Yes, this is the case we are currently facing.
"Does Not Exist Even If Spoken"... this riddle fits it perfectly.
A case where Center staff directly exterminate the urban legend.
Since other cards are exhausted, the card for this case is...
"Collapse and Judgment" which Azami-san becomes the owner of.
I wonder what kind of ending Azami-san will face.
Eh, but everyone who held this card vanished so far...
Oops, if I don't summarize the info seriously, Azami-san will get bored of me.
Illumina Cards, thought to be 6 in total.
Is all of this set up by the Manager of Samejima?
We need to summarize this information too.
How much information can we get from the Samejima site?
The Jimmers are posting from elsewhere.
It should serve for gathering SNS rumors at least.
Since we only looked at the main page, checking posts is nearly a first.
Is that so? I thought you checked various things.
First, why are Illumina Cards displayed on this site?
Let's search for anything written about the relationship between the Manager and the cards.
Oh, Manager and Cards. Read posts.
Ah, this. It's locked and looks like eyes are peering out.
Most posts here seem to be speculation too.
I heard a rumor the Manager is a genius hacker.
There are rumors they caused a crazy incident, but...
No records of the incident. Not a one.
I see, past history becomes charisma.
Oh, the one who made Illumina Cards was the Manager.
The Jimmers worship the Manager of Samejima as the one who gives chances.
Hmm, the cards were made by the Manager.
Observation of all the card prophecy contents?
We can't look through this now.
As a personal hobby, do it after this is over.
There are those observing the police movements.
Good grief, in this world you never know where you're being watched or listened to.
Something that was covered up and shouldn't exist.
The darkness of Public Security must not exist.
If they try to prove its existence...
Is that riddle a threat to Public Security?
If so, the Manager might get erased.
A post implying Public Security is maneuvering secretly.
I can't help but expect it.
Expecting the secret maneuvers of operatives.
The thread written about cards is gone.
What should I search to find it?
Cards predicting deaths of celebrities or something.
Wait, the card that became the base for Illumina Cards.
The card called the Zero-th Card.
I don't recognize that as part of the series.
Apparently there's a birth secret story of Illumina Cards handwritten by the Manager somewhere on the site.
Based on the Zero-th Card, the card that became the base for Illumina Cards?
Let's enjoy the birth secret story carefully later.
Rather, Azami-san is the one who...
More importantly, what will we do now?
I will entrust the information I compiled to Azami-san.
So I ask you to handle the rest of the investigation.
I-I've dissolved cases until now too!
I'll investigate! Let's do our best!
Then first, let me have Azami-san grasp the information I compiled.
Eh, eh, just summarizing the points in the notebook isn't enough?
I will confirm your understanding with specific answers.
But this case wasn't requested by anyone, right?
And there aren't any supernatural phenomena occurring, so...
Will we treat it as an urban legend?
Involved this many people and created a huge wave of rumors.
People are now being moved by the Manager.
When rumors circulate and take a form, that becomes an urban legend.
Ah, the earlier info was from the posts of Jimmers, the source of the rumors.
So the rumor has circulated enough to take the form of an urban legend?
It seems you received the information properly.
All information inside the Center is from the past.
The only thing that can track rumors circulating outside is the PC.
I tracked the rumors of the Jimmers reacting to the Manager's movements.
Then, it seems besides the Jimmers...
Others are moving influenced by that broadcast.
Who is moving, inspired by the Manager's broadcast that the Jimmers gossip about?
Public Security... this is Public Security, Public Security!
It was in the rumors I heard from Center-cho-san.
If the riddle the Manager threw out in the broadcast is a threat to Public Security...
The Manager might be erased. You'll get erased!
Even if that itself is just a rumor...
Actually, Public Security people like Jasmine-san are moving.
The police want to maintain the stance that nothing happened with that device.
Somewhere our eyes can't reach, Public Security might erase the Manager.
It is understandable currently that such rumors arise.
Shall we move to the next question?
Probably receiving the Manager's call to "Remember"...
There were those trying to remember past incidents.
Talking about the Happy 777 Billion Yen Leak Incident...
And "That Incident" which must not be spoken of.
You seem to grasp it well.
There were sharp ones among the Jimmers...
Why were they stopping the recollection of the past incident?
The scale is different... can't remember... will get erased.
If you try to recall and speak of the details of the incident...
"Threads that should be on SNS disappeared."
When I saw the post, I thought it was a joke, but...
Perhaps the thread was actually deleted to hide something?
Regarding the movements of Public Security that Jimmers rumor about...
To prevent confidential information from coming to light...
I guess that's what it means.
I can't imagine Jasmine-san and the others doing that though.
Of course, there are cases where rumors and reality differ.
Public Security shouldn't be monolithic either.
Actually, there was Kurosawa-san's incident too.
Not getting trapped in subjectivity, first grasp the outline of the urban legend.
That is the basic of investigation.
Then I ask about the origin of this rumor.
Whether you caught the basic characteristics of this urban legend...
This characteristic can be said to be the trigger moving Public Security.
The way the rumor originates in this urban legend...
What kind of way is it?
Rumor generation is treating what doesn't exist as existing...
Existing... treating what doesn't exist... as existing, right?
Saying "it's like this, like that" about things not happening...
Probably "treating what isn't there as being there."
Yeah, what isn't there isn't there... if it's not there, it's not.
It means treating something treated as nonexistent as existing.
Public Security, wanting to keep secrets, moves because of this rumor...
And erases people talking about this story.
And the ones hiding the secret and the ones revealing it create this urban legend.
The rumor that if you speak of an event supposed not to exist, you get erased by Public Security.
Talking about the thing itself is considered dangerous.
The urban legend conceivable from this situation...
Samejima Incident. As expected, Samejima Incident.
The site name is Samejima too.
Is it the Samejima Incident after all?
No good, everyone, searching the Samejima Incident is...
I hear sounds knocking on the window.
Did your heart skip a beat?
Please stop doing it on purpose.
Now that we spoke the urban legend name, we will be targeted by Public Security.
If you speak of an event treated as nonexistent as existing, you get erased.
U-Um, are there countermeasures or things to be careful of for the Samejima Incident?
Also, does Samejima relate to the Samejima Incident?
Do not try to reveal. Do not try to share.
If you don't speak of it in the first place, no problem occurs.
The name Samejima is likely the Manager's twist, unknown for now.
Public Security is actually moving too.
Not everyone is friendly like Jasmine.
Since we collect info for dissolution, we have no choice but to steel our resolve.
Steel our resolve... Kukuru (Gindaco), takoyaki is tasty.
Huh? Center-cho-san, I can't hear you well.
Perhaps the antis loitering in front of the Center for harassment...
Please try to move so you can stop the Manager of Samejima too.
Can't rely on Center-cho from here on.
I stop the Manager of Samejima?
No use thinking that far ahead now.
First is solving the riddle the Manager said.
But I don't get it at all right now so...
The Zero-th Card Jasmine-san left behind.
I wrote down the info from Center-cho-san in the notebook.
I should decide what to do next.
Jasmine-san who went to catch the Manager of Samejima.
She must have said Zero-th Card because she noticed something.
Maybe that meaning is the hint to the riddle.
I think this probably refers to Illumina Cards but...
The Illumina Cards were made by the Manager of Samejima in the first place.
Why did the Manager of Samejima make the Illumina Cards?
Surely something something something something perhaps.
Shirakami wanted to boast? Misfortune cards written vertically.
Wanted to prophesy the misfortune of those who held them.
I think it means wanted to prophesy, probably.
Maybe wanted to prophesy the misfortune of those who held the cards?
Wanted to boast about the quality of the cards.
Ah, wanted to boast about the quality of the cards.
Wanted to boast about the quality of the cards.
Maybe prophesied the misfortune of those who held them.
The whereabouts of everyone who held Illumina Cards so far are unknown.
If so, will misfortune befall me holding Collapse and Judgment?
Eh, wait, considering the current situation, it won't end with just me, right?
I want a bit more info on the Zero-th Card.
It's the woman from the posted photo!
Before I knew it, surrounded. Was I spacing out?
What are you doing there? What are you writing?
Is it the plan for the terror you're about to cause?
I'm trying to stop the Manager of Samejima...
She does have a connection to that Manager after all!
Not that, I am the owner of the Collapse and Judgment card!
No good, this one only has executing the prophecy in her head too!
If we stop her, we can stop the prophecy!
We won't let you cause terror!
Don't say it honestly and seriously.
I waited quite a while, Tommy.
Is there a scene riding together in the car seat~
Amazing, Azami and Tomiiri's seated height difference.
Seated height difference is also very good.
Seems she fought with the Manager and is unconscious right now.
Being kind is a wonderful thing.
But this isn't the time to be visiting her, right?
Amazing, properly saying "Being kind is a wonderful thing." Amazing.
Instead of just rejecting "No time for visits!"
Saying "That kind part of you is good, but..." As expected.
Word choice is too beautiful, fabulous.
Ah no good, I'm panicking, calm down.
Jasmine-san wouldn't want me to come here.
Tomiiri-san, do you know where Jasmine-san was investigating?
Samejima Manager and Zero-th Card... special info...
Special info on the Zero-th Card shouldn't be easily gathered.
Um, I thought you were a fluffier child but...
I came to pick you up to take you there.
What that girl investigated there, how far she went...
What she investigated, how far she reached.
A case only you can track.
Um, Tomiiri-san, where am I heading?
Because Center-cho-san said investigating this might get me erased...
I'll tell you when we reach the destination.
Also, you were surrounded by a dangerous bunch.
Is it about the password device?
Samejima and Urban Legend Dissolution Center are both trying to cause Collapse and Judgment?
It's kind of become that weird flow.
Until we reach the destination, I'll do what I can.
Brave Volunteer! Someone charged the Urban Legend Dissolution Center!
Possibility of it being their own post exists.
Vigilantes... rather, tried to catch Center staff to probe terror.
Going to raid is really a Saint?
What's pathetic is police are incompetent so...
Commoners gathering info and charging in...
Leads to early resolution? Seriously do your job.
Did anything get resolved with that commotion?
Charging in itself could be a crime.
Saying those people aren't much different from Jimmers.
I understand feeling like that though.
Only have brains to be believers huh.
Even if not black (guilty), crush if suspicious.
Even if not black, crush if suspicious.
Surely numbers increased and became radical.
Which one are they talking about?
Just like you said, Vigilantes and Jimmers aren't much different...
Numbers increasing isn't a good story either way.
Can't laugh. Bomb terror isn't a joke.
People think it's a joke or hoax but...
Better than spreading all at once.
If it becomes a panic state, it will be terrible.
Jimmers dangerous, where is safe to run? Yababa.
Certainly if we know a safe place we could have them flee but...
If we know the goal we can act ahead, but we don't know yet.
This is what Jasmine-san was saying.
Certain that Jimmers trying to execute Occult Great Reset.
Occult Great Reset is a bible for occult lovers, Jasmine-san said.
Becoming enthusiastic is wonderful but becoming fanatical...
Must not narrow vision and distort intake info.
Becomes like total affirmation of everything.
Jimmers doing it on their own...
Urban Legend Dissolution Center just hopped on the joke, right?
Not a joke or anything, haven't hopped on.
People cheering for Urban Legend Dissolution Center...
Attack people and act like heroes...
Being rough isn't good I guess.
No, affirming parts is fine to totally affirm.
Let's go with omniscient omnipotent total affirmation!
Reports prioritized info about terror incident by mysterious group...
Maybe few care if they are Jimmers or not.
Ah, why did Illumina Card boast turn into this terrible thing?
Not all Jimmers are doing terror activities.
I looked forward to urban legends coming up every time though.
I want to help with videos too.
Eyes or neck, just exposing that...
As an occult fan, surely want to expect that.
Collapsing is fine too, I think.
We must have seen various Shirakamis.
Those kids are enlightened, aren't they.
I don't fit in Great Reset either.
Did the Center issue any clear statement?
Maybe this person is a Jimmer.
Many might hope for current environment to change.
Just a whim? Why terror now?
I watched Samejima for a long time...
The "they really did it" feeling was crazy.
That should be a part of it.
Seems to be a genius hacker.
Ah, was written in the notebook too.
If such talk exists, an incident should be recorded.
Thought only Jimmers knew such talk.
If you know details of Happy 777 Billion Yen Leak Incident, please tell.
Talking about Happy Casino or something?
Never heard an incident with that name.
I see, who is that Manager?
The person in today's talk, who is inside?
Even if met at an offline meeting...
Wouldn't know who on the site the person in front is.
I have exchanged opinions on the BBS.
Spoke a little, made me think they were super smart.
If only there was recorded data.
Why make it as Illumina Cards specifically?
That person is a millionaire right?
Don't know how they earned it.
Earned with crime with that money?
Have to track what rumors are flowing.
No matter how much I search, no article appears.
Going too deep might get you erased.
Unexpectedly this delusion cannot be underestimated.
Well certainly delusion cannot be underestimated.
The riddle in video... solved yet?
Answer or hint or potent info?
How seriously does the world take it?
Sheep Man (bracket) born in Horse Year.
If I write the answer now will it buzz?
What was it? Useless to say anything problem.
What is "doesn't exist even if spoken"?
Can post answer displayed on site to site?
What happens if I post this?
Anyway some info should be obtained.
If you need anything I will prepare it, say it.
What did you say to do?
Like originally existed but gone now?
Exasperated by peaceful idiocy of timeline.
And facing the end while senile...
That riddle is likely same as prophecy.
What to do with stream and riddle?
Could be said to be the demand.
That girl's precious colleague after all.
If something happens I'll get scolded.
So I will have you track that girl's traces from here.
Reason I can only ask you, I'll explain when we arrive.
Keep the place we enter now a secret between you and me.
Various... various Tomiiri-sans seen at once, amazing.
Fukurai-san, know what a Non-Resolved Case is?
Non-Resolved Case... um... not couldn't resolve but...
Case investigation terminated for some reason...
Police Agency has a secret warehouse storing those files.
Investigating case files that went to Closet.
Possibly info on Zero-th Card is in that Closet too...
This is the one where talking gets you erased.
Investigating steadily and reaching resolution is healthy cycle.
So I can't like this place.
Like on top of these shelves...
Search while looking at numbers in huge warehouse.
I've been to stupidly huge IKEA.
Arrangement might be close to IKEA.
Before you report info found here...
If riddle answer relates to Illumina Cards...
Since she arrived at Zero-th Card here...
If unsure, call out to the Librarian there.
Zero-th Card info and info seemingly related to riddle.
Even if asked and answered, it is monologue.
Ah, it's that kind of setup.
My job is solely managing documents here.
Like the files inside her nose were overturned.
Was here but treated as not here.
Jasmine-san arrived at Zero-th Card info, right?
Investigate what she researched and did.
No, she was totally a college student, totally.
Being proper as police is good too.
Thinking of them as object to protect...
Makes me say "That's nice" even more.
Fall from 10 meters with iron plate party.
Whole body bruises and several fractures...
Was supposed to be shared after Five Society case.
If we had time, we could have tracked/investigated here...
Um, is it really okay for me to be here?
All circumstances, reasons, including my feelings...
Does that mean other police don't know we are here?
If found out, me and Librarian are fired immediately.
Don't know if I'll talk soon.
I like the perishing part too.
Aware of involving in dangerous thing.
